sentences: Prospa Ochimana was born in Northern Nigeria, Kaduna State on 6 November 1988 but originally hails from Kogi State, Nigeria.
His interest for music started when he was a child which dates as far back as 1992.
“Ekwueme”, officially released in the year 2018 was a big hit in the Nigerian music industry.
The song which featured Osinachi Nwachukwu exceeded the shores of Nigeria and was first released in a live recording at Dunamis International Gospel Church, Abuja in 2018.
Currently, Ekwueme has over 57 million streams on YouTube making it one of the most viewed Nigerian gospel songs on YouTube.
Over the years, the concert have featured other reputable gospel musical artistes like Freke Umoh, Elijah Oyelade and many more.
In 2018, he was nominated for the City People's Gospel Awards.
The Akwa Ibom Christmas Carols Festival which was convened by the Akwa Ibom State Government hosted Prospa Ochimana in their 2019 Carnival of Songs edition.

In 2019, he founded his own record label known as Torn Veil Music International which is responsible for most of his productions.
